# Development environment

Full guide: `docs/contributing/development-setup.md`

## Setup

```bash
nvm use && corepack enable
make setup
cp .env.example .env
```

## Before every PR

```bash
make check   # branch guard + CI parity validation
```

## Workflow

1. Never commit on `main` — use topic branch (`feat/`, `fix/`, etc.)
2. Husky enforces pre-commit validation and Conventional Commits
3. Local `pnpm run validate` mirrors CI

## Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `make setup` | Install deps + git hooks |
| `make check` | Full validation before PR |
| `make validate` | CI parity (oss, lint, test, build) |
| `make docker-up` | Start local infrastructure |

See `docs/contributing/development-setup.md` for workspace dev commands.

When stack is defined, extend with `test`, `build`, and integration commands.
